original_title: Acland's Video Atlas of Human Anatomy
overview: Acland's Video Atlas of Human Anatomy is a series of anatomy lessons on video presented by Robert D. Acland. The series uses unembalmed human specimens to illustrate anatomical structures.Intended for use by medical, dental and medical science students, the video teaching aid uses simple language and high quality images.
title: Acland's Video Atlas of Human Anatomy
